{"id":7341,"date":"2017-03-16T03:30:00","date_gmt":"2017-03-16T10:30:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/fundbox.com\/blog\/?p=7341"},"modified":"2019-05-09T13:36:18","modified_gmt":"2019-05-09T20:36:18","slug":"slow-payments","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/fundbox.com\/blog\/slow-payments\/","title":{"rendered":"6 Ways Slow Payments Affect Small Businesses"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>For many small businesses, slow payments are a fact of life.<\/p>\n<p>We surveyed small businesses in the U.S. to understand exactly how <a href=\"https:\/\/fundbox.com\/blog\/what-is-invoice-financing\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">unpaid invoices<\/a> affect their growth. For example, nearly a quarter of American SMBs freeze hiring when cash flow is slow.<\/p>\n<p>The opportunity cost is huge:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>If all small businesses were paid for all of their unpaid invoices, they could <strong>hire 2.1 million incremental employees<\/strong>. [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=If%20all%20SMBs%20were%20paid%20for%20all%20unpaid%20invoices%2C%20they%20could%20hire%202.1M%20new%20employees%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<li><strong>79% of small business owners choose to cut their own pay<\/strong> when customer payments are slow [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=79%25%20of%20small%20business%20owners%20choose%20to%20cut%20their%20own%20pay%20when%20customer%20payments%20are%20slow%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<li>If small businesses were paid for all of their unpaid invoices, <strong>business owners could pay themselves an incremental $31k<\/strong> on average [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=If%20SMBs%20were%20paid%20for%20all%20unpaid%20invoices%2C%20business%20owners%20could%20pay%20themselves%20%2B%2431k%20on%20avg%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>How does your business compare?<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-7365 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/fundbox.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/6-ways-slow-payments-affect-small-business_infographic_FINAL-01.png\" alt=\"6 ways slow payments affect small business Fundbox infographic\" width=\"2084\" height=\"16952\" srcset=\"https:\/\/fundbox.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/6-ways-slow-payments-affect-small-business_infographic_FINAL-01.png 2084w, https:\/\/fundbox.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/6-ways-slow-payments-affect-small-business_infographic_FINAL-01-768x6247.png 768w, https:\/\/fundbox.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/6-ways-slow-payments-affect-small-business_infographic_FINAL-01-189x1536.png 189w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2084px) 100vw, 2084px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h1><strong>Tired of paying the price for slow payments? We can help. <a href=\"https:\/\/app.fundbox.com\/login?utm_source=blog&amp;utm_medium=content&amp;utm_campaign=unpaid-invoices\">Sign up for Fundbox<\/a>.<\/strong><\/h1>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<h2><strong>Small Business Hiring<\/strong><\/h2>\n<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>23% of small businesses cut hiring<\/strong> new employees when customer payments are slow [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=23%25%20of%20small%20businesses%20cut%20hiring%20new%20employees%20when%20customer%20payments%20are%20slow%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<li>If all small businesses were paid for all of their unpaid invoices, they could hire <strong>2.1 million incremental employees<\/strong>.\u00a0[<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=If%20all%20SMBs%20were%20paid%20for%20all%20unpaid%20invoices%2C%20they%20could%20hire%202.1M%20new%20employees%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>\n<h2><strong>Business Owners Take a Pay Cut<\/strong><\/h2>\n<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>79% of small business owners choose to cut their own pay<\/strong> when customer payments are slow [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=79%25%20of%20small%20business%20owners%20choose%20to%20cut%20their%20own%20pay%20when%20customer%20payments%20are%20slow%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<li>If small businesses were paid for all of their unpaid invoices, <strong>business owners could pay themselves an incremental $31k<\/strong> on average [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=If%20SMBs%20were%20paid%20for%20all%20unpaid%20invoices%2C%20business%20owners%20could%20pay%20themselves%20%2B%2431k%20on%20avg%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ol start=\"3\">\n<li>\n<h2><strong>No New Equipment<\/strong><\/h2>\n<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>23% of small businesses would hold off on buying new equipment<\/strong> if customer payments were slow [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=23%25%20of%20SMBs%20would%20hold%20off%20on%20buying%20new%20equipment%20if%20customer%20payments%20were%20slow%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<li>If small businesses were paid for all of their unpaid invoices, they could <strong>purchase an average of $9.2k in new equipment<\/strong>t [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=If%20SMBs%20were%20paid%20for%20all%20unpaid%20invoices%2C%20they%20could%20purchase%20avg%20of%20%249.2k%20in%20new%20equipment%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n<li>\n<h2><strong>Reduced Marketing Budget<\/strong><\/h2>\n<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>20% of small businesses cut marketing and growth efforts<\/strong> when customer payments are slow [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=20%25%20of%20small%20businesses%20cut%20marketing%20and%20growth%20efforts%20when%20customer%20payments%20are%20slow%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<li>If small businesses were paid for all of their unpaid invoices, they could <strong>invest $8.3k more in marketing and growth<\/strong> [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=If%20SMBs%20were%20paid%20for%20all%20unpaid%20invoices%2C%20they%20could%20invest%20%2B%248.3k%20more%20in%20marketing%2Fgrowth%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ol start=\"5\">\n<li>\n<h2><strong>Payroll Takes a Hit<\/strong><\/h2>\n<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>18% of small businesses hold back on pay increases<\/strong> when customer payments are slow [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=18%25%20of%20small%20businesses%20hold%20back%20on%20pay%20increases%20when%20customer%20payments%20are%20slow%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<li>If small businesses were paid for all of their unpaid invoices, they could <strong>spend $7.4k more on employee salaries<\/strong> [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=If%20SMBs%20were%20paid%20for%20all%20unpaid%20invoices%2C%20they%20could%20spend%20%247.4k%20more%20on%20employee%20salaries%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ol start=\"6\">\n<li>\n<h2><strong>Decreased Inventory<\/strong><\/h2>\n<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>17% of small businesses cut spending on inventory<\/strong> when customer payments are slow [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=17%25%20of%20small%20businesses%20cut%20spending%20on%20inventory%20when%20customer%20payments%20are%20slow%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<li>If small businesses were paid for all of their unpaid invoices, they could <strong>invest an incremental $6.7k in inventory<\/strong> [<a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/intent\/tweet?text=If%20SMBs%20were%20paid%20for%20all%20unpaid%20invoices%2C%20they%20could%20invest%20an%20add%27l%20%246.7k%20in%20inventory%20http%3A%2F%2Ffbx.bz%2FSlowPayments%20pic.twitter.com\/mxjtxa7Bz0\">Tweet this<\/a>]<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Copy &amp; Paste to Share on Your Site<\/strong><br \/>\n<textarea style=\"width: 600px; height: 100px;\">&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please include attribution to fundbox.com with this graphic.&lt;\/strong&lt;a href=https:\/\/fundbox.com\/blog\/slow-payments?utm_source=blog&amp;utm_medium=content&amp;utm_campaign=slow-payments_infographic_share&gt;&lt;img src=https:\/\/fundbox.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/6-ways-slow-payments-affect-small-business_infographic_FINAL-01.png alt=&#8217;Fundbox Infographic: 6 Ways Slow Payments Affect Small Businesses&#8217; width=&#8217;540px&#8217; border=&#8217;0&#8217;\/&gt;&lt;\/a&gt;<\/textarea><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>For many small businesses, slow payments are a fact of life. We surveyed small businesses in the U.S. to understand &#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":6,"featured_media":11990,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[21],"tags":[72,11532],"yst_prominent_words":[1347,1337,1354,1331,1367,1341,1325,1324,1335,1398,1339,1353,1350,1333,1327,1343,1329,759,1345,1399],"post-meta-fields":{"stripe_selected":null,"preview_color":null,"bw_feature":null,"category_color":null},"yoast_title":"6 Ways Slow Payments Affect Small Businesses | Fundbox Blog","yoast_meta":[{"name":"description","content":"For many small businesses, slow payments are a fact of life. Fundbox surveyed small businesses across the U.S., and the opportunity cost is huge."},{"property"